{
 "name": "RPlog_Futile_Research_-_Reading_3",
 "title": "Futile Research: The Emissary",
 "summary": "On the steps of the Government Complex, the refugee girl Arise -- after retrieving her monitor droid from a Sullustan guard -- falls into conversation with Evir, a diplomatic emissary from the ocean world of Wann Tsir. They bond over a shared love of open air, forests, and oceans, and over their homeworlds' experience of Imperial occupation; Evir's people fought the Empire off after fifteen years, around the time of Endor. Arise presses him on courage, destiny, and why adults are so fearful for children, and Evir counsels that learning makes one more helpful and that doing one's part is all anyone can expect. When Arise reveals her mother was arrested by the Empire during the conquest of Chandrila and that she is now a ward of Social Services, Evir is reminded of an orphaned niece his family adopted after their own liberation. The two share a warm, melancholy exchange before parting, Evir off to collect a sealed package from the Tsiran embassy and Arise back to her studies, still hoping to find a place to call home.",
